The Necropolis lived up to its name. Skeletons clad in rusted gold armor—Gilded Husks—crawled from the sand. Lyra’s arrows turned the front line into a bonfire, but the numbers were overwhelming.
"They’re endless!" Kaelen Draken shouted from the other flank, his spear flashing. "We need to fall back!"
"No," Cian muttered. He saw his opening. The Professor was occupied with a group of Elite Husks near the entrance.
Cian grabbed Lyra’s wrist. "Follow me. Now!"
They ducked into a side passage, Narrowly avoiding a collapsing pillar. As soon as they were out of sight, Cian released the tether on his power.
"Vanguard, Shadow-Step."
His shadow elongated, splitting into three distinct forms. Vanguard 01 took the lead, its purple blade carving a path through the Husks with terrifying efficiency. Two new, smaller shadows—Wraiths he had harvested during his midnight training—flitted through the walls, scouting the path ahead.
"They're... they're like your own private army," Lyra breathed, her eyes wide as she watched a Wraith snap the neck of a skeleton archer before it could aim at her.
"They’re more than that," Cian said, his eyes glowing. "They’re the only ones I can trust not to report me to the Council."
They reached the hidden alcove. It was a small, circular room covered in ancient runes that hummed in a frequency only Cian could hear. In the center, resting on a pedestal of bone, was a silver locket.
As Cian reached for it, the ground shook.
A massive, golden-plated hand smashed through the ceiling. The Gilded King, the dungeon boss, had sensed an intruder in its private sanctum.
